domain_metadata.value: (1) The locations in this dataset are not “real time,” meaning they are not necessarily active on the date of viewing this dataset. (2) Due to varying performance and reporting periods and requirements, both across and within CNCS programs, some data values may appear as zero or blank in this dataset. (3) Location data is masked so as not to reveal the exact street address of potentially sensitive service sites and programs. The location remains in the general vicinity of the actual location. Some sites may be completely masked due to beneficiary privacy concerns. (4) Services may be provided at some Program/Project Locations as well as Service Locations, either by members and volunteers or by the organization directly. (5) The ‘AmeriCorps Territory’ code does not include the U.S. Territories Guam or Puerto Rico, which are managed as AmeriCorps State Competitive and AmeriCorps State Formula awards. (6) The ‘AmeriCorps State Without Commission’ code is for single state direct project relationships between CNCS and the grantee. These can include programs operating in a state without a state commission or some special program types, such as some justice AmeriCorps programs. (7) ‘AmeriCorps Indian Tribes’ may not include all awards to tribal entities. (8) Locations data found in the dataset that are not rendering on maps may have latitude/longitude or underlying address inaccuracies. (9) All other limitations and notations relevant to the CNCS State Profiles 2016-2017 reports are attributable to this dataset. For more information, see Source Link. (10) CNCS is not responsible for the quality or accuracy of analyses and reports created from this dataset by non-CNCS entities.

domain_metadata.value: (1) Includes all Segal AmeriCorps Education payment types, including interest payments. (2) Institution, System, and State are data values reviewed and cleaned by CNCS staff to increase standardization. The cleaning process includes multiple types of changes including; adjusting abbreviations, fixing spelling errors,  updating the name if ownership changed or as otherwise changed by the institution, or reflecting the name of the higher ed institution if payment was handled by a loan processing organization but the higher ed institution name was present in CNCS records associated with the payment, among other change types. (3) Changes are current as of September 2017 and are subject to change on further review. (4) Changes do not affect the CNCS system of record managed by the National Service Trust and are made for the purpose of easier public consumption of the data. (5) Systems may be incomplete or missing. If you believe a system should be added to the dataset or if another record is in error, please write to opendata@cns.gov with the current name and state of the institution and the recommended change. (6) Payment to eligible institutions is made on behalf of the AmeriCorps member or recipient of transferred awards at their request. AmeriCorps members must use their award within seven years of completing their term of service. Recipients of transferred awards must use the award within ten years from the date the education award was earned. (7) Repay loan payments are those made to qualified student loans. Qualified student loans is defined as a loan backed by the federal government under Title IV of the Higher Education Act (except PLUS Loans to parents of students) or under Titles VII or VIII of the Public Health Service Act. Under this category, AmeriCorps alumni may also use their Segal AmeriCorps Education Award to repay a student loan that was made to the member by a state agency, including state institutions of higher education. (8) Eligible schools for education payments are higher educational institut

AmeriCorps Segal Education Award payment data is collected and maintained by the National Service Trust. Payment to eligible institutions is made on behalf of the AmeriCorps member or recipient of a transferred award at their request. AmeriCorps members must use their award within seven years of completing their term of service. Recipients of transferred awards must use the award within ten years from the date the education award was earned.

domain_metadata.value: (1) Includes all Segal AmeriCorps Education payment types, including interest payments. (2) Institution, System, and State are data values reviewed and cleaned by CNCS staff to increase standardization. The cleaning process includes multiple types of changes including; adjusting abbreviations, fixing spelling errors,  updating the name if ownership changed or as otherwise changed by the institution, or reflecting the name of the higher ed institution if payment was handled by a loan processing organization but the higher ed institution name was present in CNCS records associated with the payment, among other change types. (3) Changes are current as of September 2017 and are subject to change on further review. (4) Changes do not affect the CNCS system of record managed by the National Service Trust and are made for the purpose of easier public consumption of the data. (5) Systems may be incomplete or missing. If you believe a system should be added to the dataset or if another record is in error, please write to opendata@cns.gov with the current name and state of the institution and the recommended change. (6) Payment to eligible institutions is made on behalf of the AmeriCorps member or recipient of transferred awards at their request. AmeriCorps members must use their award within seven years of completing their term of service. Recipients of transferred awards must use the award within ten years from the date the education award was earned. (7) Repay loan payments are those made to qualified student loans. Qualified student loans is defined as a loan backed by the federal government under Title IV of the Higher Education Act (except PLUS Loans to parents of students) or under Titles VII or VIII of the Public Health Service Act. Under this category, AmeriCorps alumni may also use their Segal AmeriCorps Education Award to repay a student loan that was made to the member by a state agency, including state institutions of higher education. (8) Eligible schools for education payments are higher educational institut

Payment to eligible institutions is made on behalf of the AmeriCorps member or recipient of a transferred award at their request. AmeriCorps members must use their award within seven years of completing their term of service. Recipients of transferred awards must use the award within ten years from the date the education award was earned.

resource.name: AmeriCorps Members Demographic
resource.description:
The data is prepared using AmeriCorps members who began service on any day in fiscal year (FY) 2017. The members may have served 1 to 365 days during their term. Members who are in never served, disqualified, pre-service, or deferred statuses were excluded from this analysis. 
AmeriCorps VISTA and AmeriCorps NCCC race and ethnicity data come from the member application to serve. The code to extract the data between the two programs is the same. 
The ASN race and ethnicity data comes from the enrollment form. The enrollment form may exist multiple times if the member enrolled in more than one term. It is not uncommon for each enrollment form to have conflicting information about the member’s race and ethnicity. The member may have enrollment form data for terms served outside of the timeframe of the dataset. For example, if we are reporting on members who began service in FY17, then a member who also served in FY16 may have race and ethnicity information in the FY16 enrollment form and no race or ethnicity information or conflicting information in the FY17 enrollment form. In the case of conflicting information, this analysis assumes each instance of race designation is correct. If a member reports themselves as “Asian or Asian American” in one enrollment form and “White” in another enrollment form, then the analysis categorizes this person as someone who identifies with multiple race selections vs. one or the other. In the case of ethnicity, if a member indicates that they are not Hispanic or Latino/a in one form, but that they are in another, this analysis assumes the affirmative—and they will be categorized as Hispanic or Latino/a. Lastly, the totals include the total results from the query plus the difference between the query and the raw count of members who started service in that fiscal year. The members who did not have a record in the invite table and enrollment table were added to the non-response category. 
Senior Corps Figures come from the Annual Progress Report Supplement as of April 11, 2018. 
Percentages are calculated from totals of the subcategories, excluding the non-response categories.

resource.description:
The purpose of the Member Exit Survey is to collect information about AmeriCorps members’ experiences.  All exiting AmeriCorps State and National, VISTA, and NCCC members who complete a term of service are invited to complete the survey.  

- A copy of the complete survey questions is provided as an attachment. 
- Responses from Question 2, Question 27, and  all open-ended questions are excluded. 
- Responses from Northern Mariana Islands and Guam are combined. 
- Responses from Virgin Islands and Puerto Rico are combined.

domain_metadata.value: (1) The locations in this dataset are not “real time,” meaning they are not necessarily active on the date of viewing this dataset. (2) Due to varying performance and reporting periods and requirements, both across and within CNCS programs, some data values may appear as zero or blank in this dataset. (3) Location data is masked so as not to reveal the exact street address of potentially sensitive service sites and programs. The location remains in the general vicinity of the actual location. Some sites may be completely masked due to beneficiary privacy concerns. (4) Services may be provided at some Program/Project Locations as well as Service Locations, either by members and volunteers or by the organization directly. (5) The ‘AmeriCorps Territory’ code does not include the U.S. Territories Guam or Puerto Rico, which are managed as AmeriCorps State Competitive and AmeriCorps State Formula awards. (6) The ‘AmeriCorps State Without Commission’ code is for single state direct project relationships between CNCS and the grantee. These can include programs operating in a state without a state commission or some special program types, such as some justice AmeriCorps programs. (7) ‘AmeriCorps Indian Tribes’ may not include all awards to tribal entities. (8) Locations data found in the dataset that are not rendering on maps may have latitude/longitude or underlying address inaccuracies. (9) All other limitations and notations relevant to the CNCS State Profiles 2016-2017 reports are attributable to this dataset. For more information, see Source Link. (10) CNCS is not responsible for the quality or accuracy of analyses and reports created from this dataset by non-CNCS entities.
This dataset comes from administrative data provided to CNCS by grantee/sponsor organizations.

domain_metadata.value: (1) The locations in this dataset are not “real time,” meaning they are not necessarily active on the date of viewing this dataset. (2) Due to varying performance and reporting periods and requirements, both across and within CNCS programs, some data values may appear as zero or blank in this dataset. (3) Location data is masked so as not to reveal the exact street address of potentially sensitive service sites and programs. The location remains in the general vicinity of the actual location. Some sites may be completely masked due to beneficiary privacy concerns. (4) Services may be provided at some Program/Project Locations as well as Service Locations, either by members and volunteers or by the organization directly. (5) The ‘AmeriCorps Territory’ code does not include the U.S. Territories Guam or Puerto Rico, which are managed as AmeriCorps State Competitive and AmeriCorps State Formula awards. (6) The ‘AmeriCorps State Without Commission’ code is for single state direct project relationships between CNCS and the grantee. These can include programs operating in a state without a state commission or some special program types, such as some justice AmeriCorps programs. (7) ‘AmeriCorps Indian Tribes’ may not include all awards to tribal entities. (8) Locations data found in the dataset that are not rendering on maps may have latitude/longitude or underlying address inaccuracies. (9) All other limitations and notations relevant to the CNCS State Profiles 2016-2017 reports are attributable to this dataset. For more information, see Source Link. (10) CNCS is not responsible for the quality or accuracy of analyses and reports created from this dataset by non-CNCS entities.
This dataset comes from administrative data provided to CNCS by grantee/sponsor organizations.

domain_metadata.value: (1) Includes all Segal AmeriCorps Education payment types, including interest payments. (2) Payment subcategories rounded down to hundred thousand place. (3) Total payments calculated as sum of rounded subcategories. (4) Individual count is rounded down to hundreds place and represents distinct count of unique individuals. Individuals expend across State and payment type boundaries. Total count of individuals will not equal sum of sub category values. (5) State derived from higher education and loan holding institution address. State assignments current as of May 3, 2017 and are subject to change in future reporting which could affect State totals. (6) International mailing, Unassigned State, APO, Northern Mariana Islands, Guam, Virgin Islands, and American Samoa were not included in this analysis. (7) Reimbursements and payment cancellation adjustments are distributed evenly amongst payment subcategories pre rounding. (8) $3.2 million in payments made by 2,900 individuals since 1994 were not able to be categorized as either Education Payments or Loan Repayments and are not included in the totals. (9) Payment to eligible institutions is made on behalf of the AmeriCorps member or recipient of transferred awards at their request. AmeriCorps members must use their award within seven years of completing their term of service. Recipients of transferred awards must use the award within ten years from the date the education award was earned. (10) Loan payments are those made to qualified student loans. Qualified student loans is defined as a loan backed by the federal government under Title IV of the Higher Education Act (except PLUS Loans to parents of students) or under Titles VII or VIII of the Public Health Service Act. Under this category, AmeriCorps alumni may also use their Segal AmeriCorps Education Award to repay a student loan that was made to the member by a state agency, including state institutions of higher education. The total number of unduplicated AmeriCorps Alumni who authorized the payment. Subcategories may not equal totals in parent categories due to individuals making multiple payments across years and institutions.

domain_metadata.value: (1) Includes all Segal AmeriCorps Education payment types, including interest payments. (2) Institution, System, and State are data values reviewed and cleaned by CNCS staff to increase standardization. The cleaning process includes multiple types of changes including; adjusting abbreviations, fixing spelling errors,  updating the name if ownership changed or as otherwise changed by the institution, or reflecting the name of the higher ed institution if payment was handled by a loan processing organization but the higher ed institution name was present in CNCS records associated with the payment, among other change types. (3) Changes are current as of September 2017 and are subject to change on further review. (4) Changes do not affect the CNCS system of record managed by the National Service Trust and are made for the purpose of easier public consumption of the data. (5) Systems may be incomplete or missing. If you believe a system should be added to the dataset or if another record is in error, please write to opendata@cns.gov with the current name and state of the institution and the recommended change. (6) Payment to eligible institutions is made on behalf of the AmeriCorps member or recipient of transferred awards at their request. AmeriCorps members must use their award within seven years of completing their term of service. Recipients of transferred awards must use the award within ten years from the date the education award was earned. (7) Repay loan payments are those made to qualified student loans. Qualified student loans is defined as a loan backed by the federal government under Title IV of the Higher Education Act (except PLUS Loans to parents of students) or under Titles VII or VIII of the Public Health Service Act. Under this category, AmeriCorps alumni may also use their Segal AmeriCorps Education Award to repay a student loan that was made to the member by a state agency, including state institutions of higher education. AmeriCorps members must use their award within seven years of completing their term of service. Recipients of transferred awards must use the award within ten years from the date the education award was earned.

(3) Total payments calculated as sum of rounded subcategories. (4) Individual count is rounded down to hundreds place and represents distinct count of unique individuals. Individuals expend across State and payment type boundaries. Total count of individuals will not equal sum of sub category values. (5) State derived from higher education and loan holding institution address. State assignments current as of May 3, 2017 and are subject to change in future reporting which could affect State totals. (6) International mailing, Unassigned State, APO, Northern Mariana Islands, Guam, Virgin Islands, and American Samoa were not included in this analysis. (7) Reimbursements and payment cancellation adjustments are distributed evenly amongst payment subcategories pre rounding. (8) $3.2 million in payments made by 2,900 individuals since 1994 were not able to be categorized as either Education Payments or Loan Repayments and are not included in the totals. (9) Payment to eligible institutions is made on behalf of the AmeriCorps member or recipient of transferred awards at their request. AmeriCorps members must use their award within seven years of completing their term of service. Recipients of transferred awards must use the award within ten years from the date the education award was earned. (10) Loan payments are those made to qualified student loans. Qualified student loans is defined as a loan backed by the federal government under Title IV of the Higher Education Act (except PLUS Loans to parents of students) or under Titles VII or VIII of the Public Health Service Act. Under this category, AmeriCorps alumni may also use their Segal AmeriCorps Education Award to repay a student loan that was made to the member by a state agency, including state institutions of higher education. domain_metadata.value: (1) Includes all Segal AmeriCorps Education payment types, including interest payments. (2) Institution, System, Campus, College, and State are data values were reviewed and cleaned by CNCS staff to increase standardization. The cleaning process includes multiple types of changes including; adjusting abbreviations, fixing spelling errors,  updating the name if ownership changed or as otherwise changed by the institution, or reflecting the name of the higher ed institution if payment was handled by a loan processing organization but the higher ed institution name was present in CNCS records associated with the payment, among other change types. (3) Changes are current as of September 2017 and are subject to change on further review. (4) Changes do not affect the CNCS system of record managed by the National Service Trust and are made for the purpose of easier public consumption of the data. (5) Systems, campus, and colleges may be incomplete or missing. If you believe a system should be added to the dataset or if another record is in error, please write to opendata@cns.gov with the current name and state of the institution and the recommended change. (6) Payments by payment type may be either positive or negative. The sum of all payments per institution will reflect the accurate total per the institution without further additional adjustments to the payment value. (7) Count of payments includes returned or canceled payments ($0). (8) Payment to eligible institutions is made on behalf of the AmeriCorps member or recipient of transferred awards at their request. AmeriCorps members must use their award within seven years of completing their term of service. Recipients of transferred awards must use the award within ten years from the date the education award was earned. (9) Repay loan payments are those made to qualified student loans. Qualified student loans is defined as a loan backed by the federal government under Title IV of the Higher Education Act (except PLUS Loans to parents of students) or under Titles VII

Payment to eligible institutions is made on behalf of the AmeriCorps member or recipient of a transferred award at their request. Recipients of transferred awards must use the award within ten years from the date the education award was earned.

resource.name: Employers of National Service Map
resource.description:
Employers of National Service connects AmeriCorps and Peace Corps alumni with employers from the private, public, and nonprofit sectors.

Through this initiative, employers have increased access to a dedicated, highly qualified, and mission-oriented pool of potential employees, and national service alumni have additional opportunities to apply their skills in the workplace.

More than 500 employers are now a part of the Employers of National Service program which recognizes the valuable skills gained by more 1 million Americans who have participated in AmeriCorps since 1994 and the 215,000 who have participated in the Peace Corps since 1961.

resource.name: Employers of National Service
resource.description:
Employers of National Service connects AmeriCorps and Peace Corps alumni with employers from the private, public, and nonprofit sectors.

Through this initiative, employers have increased access to a dedicated, highly qualified, and mission-oriented pool of potential employees, and national service alumni have additional opportunities to apply their skills in the workplace.

More than 500 employers are now a part of the Employers of National Service program which recognizes the valuable skills gained by more 1 million Americans who have participated in AmeriCorps since 1994 and the 215,000 who have participated in the Peace Corps since 1961.

domain_metadata.value: (1) Includes all Segal AmeriCorps Education payment types, including interest payments. (2) Institution, System, and State are data values reviewed and cleaned by CNCS staff to increase standardization. The cleaning process includes multiple types of changes including; adjusting abbreviations, fixing spelling errors,  updating the name if ownership changed or as otherwise changed by the institution, or reflecting the name of the higher ed institution if payment was handled by a loan processing organization but the higher ed institution name was present in CNCS records associated with the payment, among other change types. (3) Changes are current as of September 2017 and are subject to change on further review. (4) Changes do not affect the CNCS system of record managed by the National Service Trust and are made for the purpose of easier public consumption of the data. (5) Systems may be incomplete or missing. If you believe a system should be added to the dataset or if another record is in error, please write to opendata@cns.gov with the current name and state of the institution and the recommended change. (6) Payment to eligible institutions is made on behalf of the AmeriCorps member or recipient of transferred awards at their request. AmeriCorps members must use their award within seven years of completing their term of service. Recipients of transferred awards must use the award within ten years from the date the education award was earned. (7) Repay loan payments are those made to qualified student loans. Qualified student loans is defined as a loan backed by the federal government under Title IV of the Higher Education Act (except PLUS Loans to parents of students) or under Titles VII or VIII of the Public Health Service Act. Under this category, AmeriCorps alumni may also use their Segal AmeriCorps Education Award to repay a student loan that was made to the member by a state agency, including state institutions of higher education. (8) Eligible schools for education payments are higher educational institut

resource.attribution: Corporation for National and Community Service
columns_description: The total amount of Segal AmeriCorps Education Award and Interest payments made to the institution.
Abbreviation of the U.S. State or Territory. (INTL indicates international payment).
Name of the higher education or loan processing institution or recipient.

The total number of unduplicated AmeriCorps Alumni who authorized the payment. Subcategories may not equal totals in parent categories due to individuals making multiple payments across years and institutions.

domain_metadata.value: (1) Includes all Segal AmeriCorps Education payment types, including interest payments. (2) Institution, System, and State are data values reviewed and cleaned by CNCS staff to increase standardization. The cleaning process includes multiple types of changes including; adjusting abbreviations, fixing spelling errors,  updating the name if ownership changed or as otherwise changed by the institution, or reflecting the name of the higher ed institution if payment was handled by a loan processing organization but the higher ed institution name was present in CNCS records associated with the payment, among other change types. (3) Changes are current as of September 2017 and are subject to change on further review. (4) Changes do not affect the CNCS system of record managed by the National Service Trust and are made for the purpose of easier public consumption of the data. (5) Systems may be incomplete or missing. If you believe a system should be added to the dataset or if another record is in error, please write to opendata@cns.gov with the current name and state of the institution and the recommended change. (6) Payment to eligible institutions is made on behalf of the AmeriCorps member or recipient of transferred awards at their request. AmeriCorps members must use their award within seven years of completing their term of service. Recipients of transferred awards must use the award within ten years from the date the education award was earned. (7) Repay loan payments are those made to qualified student loans. Qualified student loans is defined as a loan backed by the federal government under Title IV of the Higher Education Act (except PLUS Loans to parents of students) or under Titles VII or VIII of the Public Health Service Act. Under this category, AmeriCorps alumni may also use their Segal AmeriCorps Education Award to repay a student loan that was made to the member by a state agency, including state institutions of higher education. (8) Eligible schools for education payments are higher educational institut

AmeriCorps Segal Education Award payment data is collected and maintained by the National Service Trust. Payment to eligible institutions is made on behalf of the AmeriCorps member or recipient of a transferred award at their request. AmeriCorps members must use their award within seven years of completing their term of service. Recipients of transferred awards must use the award within ten years from the date the education award was earned.

columns_description: The total amount of Segal AmeriCorps Education Award and Interest payments made to the institution.

The total number of unduplicated AmeriCorps Alumni who authorized the payment. Subcategories may not equal totals in parent categories due to individuals making multiple payments across years and institutions.
Abbreviation of the U.S. State or Territory. (INTL indicates international payment).
Name of the higher education or loan processing institution or recipient.

domain_metadata.value: (1) Includes all Segal AmeriCorps Education payment types, including interest payments. (2) Institution, System, and State are data values reviewed and cleaned by CNCS staff to increase standardization. The cleaning process includes multiple types of changes including; adjusting abbreviations, fixing spelling errors,  updating the name if ownership changed or as otherwise changed by the institution, or reflecting the name of the higher ed institution if payment was handled by a loan processing organization but the higher ed institution name was present in CNCS records associated with the payment, among other change types. (3) Changes are current as of September 2017 and are subject to change on further review. (4) Changes do not affect the CNCS system of record managed by the National Service Trust and are made for the purpose of easier public consumption of the data. (5) Systems may be incomplete or missing. If you believe a system should be added to the dataset or if another record is in error, please write to opendata@cns.gov with the current name and state of the institution and the recommended change. (6) Payment to eligible institutions is made on behalf of the AmeriCorps member or recipient of transferred awards at their request. AmeriCorps members must use their award within seven years of completing their term of service. Recipients of transferred awards must use the award within ten years from the date the education award was earned. (7) Repay loan payments are those made to qualified student loans. Qualified student loans is defined as a loan backed by the federal government under Title IV of the Higher Education Act (except PLUS Loans to parents of students) or under Titles VII or VIII of the Public Health Service Act. Under this category, AmeriCorps alumni may also use their Segal AmeriCorps Education Award to repay a student loan that was made to the member by a state agency, including state institutions of higher education. (8) Eligible schools for education payments are higher educational institut

resource.name: Education Award Alumni Count - Northern Marianas
resource.description: Summary dataset of total payments made to higher education and loan holding institutions from Fiscal Year 1995 through Fiscal Year 2016, aggregated by institution.
resource.attribution: Corporation for National and Community Service
columns_description: The total number of unduplicated AmeriCorps Alumni who authorized the payment. Subcategories may not equal totals in parent categories due to individuals making multiple payments across years and institutions.
The total amount of Segal AmeriCorps Education Award and Interest payments made to the institution.
Name of the higher education or loan processing institution or recipient.
Abbreviation of the U.S. State or Territory. (INTL indicates international payment).

domain_metadata.value: (1) Includes all Segal AmeriCorps Education payment types, including interest payments. (2) Institution, System, and State are data values reviewed and cleaned by CNCS staff to increase standardization. The cleaning process includes multiple types of changes including; adjusting abbreviations, fixing spelling errors,  updating the name if ownership changed or as otherwise changed by the institution, or reflecting the name of the higher ed institution if payment was handled by a loan processing organization but the higher ed institution name was present in CNCS records associated with the payment, among other change types. (3) Changes are current as of September 2017 and are subject to change on further review. (4) Changes do not affect the CNCS system of record managed by the National Service Trust and are made for the purpose of easier public consumption of the data. (5) Systems may be incomplete or missing. If you believe a system should be added to the dataset or if another record is in error, please write to opendata@cns.gov with the current name and state of the institution and the recommended change. (6) Payment to eligible institutions is made on behalf of the AmeriCorps member or recipient of transferred awards at their request. AmeriCorps members must use their award within seven years of completing their term of service. Recipients of transferred awards must use the award within ten years from the date the education award was earned. (7) Repay loan payments are those made to qualified student loans. Qualified student loans is defined as a loan backed by the federal government under Title IV of the Higher Education Act (except PLUS Loans to parents of students) or under Titles VII or VIII of the Public Health Service Act. Under this category, AmeriCorps alumni may also use their Segal AmeriCorps Education Award to repay a student loan that was made to the member by a state agency, including state institutions of higher education. (8) Eligible schools for education payments are higher educational institut

AmeriCorps Segal Education Award payment data is collected and maintained by the National Service Trust. Payment to eligible institutions is made on behalf of the AmeriCorps member or recipient of a transferred award at their request. AmeriCorps members must use their award within seven years of completing their term of service. Recipients of transferred awards must use the award within ten years from the date the education award was earned.
